-- Huijin to Sell $11.8 Billion of Bonds Early as Next Month, Daily Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-24T23:14:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/huijin-to-sell-11-8-billion-of-bonds-early-as-next-month-daily-reports.html

          
          
             Central Huijin Investment Co. plans
to sell 80 billion yuan ($11.8 billion) of bonds as early as
next month, the China Daily reported today, citing an
unidentified person close to the matter.  
 Funds raised from the sale will be injected into Export-
Import Bank of China and China Export & Credit Insurance Corp.
to strengthen their capital, the Beijing-based English-language
newspaper reported. Five brokerages including Citic Securities
Co. have been selected to underwrite the sale, the newspaper
reported.  
          
          


  


        